OverTheWire - Bandit Level 1 -> 2

1. Objective
The password for the next level is stored in a file called - located in the home directory

2. Commands Used

cat ./

3. Key Concepts Used

1. cat is a keyterm used to read any file and paste its content in the terminal itself
2. We would use ./ since 
   2.1 dot (.) indicates the current directory and when we write ./ we saying in this current directory please find this file something similar could be like Desktop/xyz which means in directory Desktop open xyz file

The reason we use it is (-) has a special function and if we just write "cat -" the sys would register it as "read from standard input" rather then check if its a file name
